Transform a 'kmeans' object into a flextable

Source: R/as_flextable.R
as_flextable.kmeans.Rd

produce a flextable describing a kmeans object. The function is only using package 'broom' that provides the data presented in the resulting flextable.

Usage

# S3 method for class 'kmeans'
as_flextable(x, digits = 4, ...)

Arguments

x

a kmeans() object

digits

number of digits for the numeric columns

...

unused argument

See also

Other as_flextable methods: as_flextable(), as_flextable.data.frame(), as_flextable.gam(), as_flextable.glm(), as_flextable.grouped_data(), as_flextable.htest(), as_flextable.lm(), as_flextable.merMod(), as_flextable.pam(), as_flextable.summarizor(), as_flextable.table(), as_flextable.tabular(), as_flextable.tabulator(), as_flextable.xtable()

Examples

if (require("stats")) {
  cl <- kmeans(scale(mtcars[1:7]), 5)
  ft <- as_flextable(cl)
  ft
}
